{"id":1736907,"retrievedAt":"2026-07-24T12:40:15.441Z","response":{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":null,"belongs_to_collection":null,"budget":0,"genres":[],"homepage":"","id":1736907,"imdb_id":null,"origin_country":["US"],"original_language":"en","original_title":"Hati Yang Tersakiti","overview":"# Translation  Mona and Farah have been close friends since they studied at college. After several years, they meet again. Mona now lives happily with her husband, Haris, although they have not yet been blessed with children. However, the marriage built on trust begins to waver. Can it be saved and the long-established friendship be cherished? Or will there be heartbreak?  Haris (Remy Ishak) was formerly a postman. Thanks to his efforts, he has now become a successful information technology (IT) entrepreneur. Mona (Nad Zainal) is a college graduate who works as an events consultant. Haris and Mona's first meeting at college sparked love, but Farah (Mimi Lana) felt that Haris was not worthy and not on par with the highly educated Mona. Farah had introduced Mona to a Datuk's son, and she herself chose the son of a Tan Sri as her husband. Farah did not invite Mona to her wedding. She also did not attend Mona's wedding, claiming work commitments.","popularity":0,"poster_path":"/mg9SukQwwhxChTRe9oEPDwCJPFD.jpg","production_companies":[{"id":140339,"logo_path":null,"name":"Art Ornament Sdn Bhd","origin_country":""}],"production_countries":[],"release_date":"2020-01-01","revenue":0,"runtime":0,"softcore":false,"spoken_languages":[],"status":"Released","tagline":"","title":"Hati Yang Tersakiti","video":false,"vote_average":0,"vote_count":0,"alternative_titles":{"titles":[]},"credits":{"cast":[{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":1109288,"known_for_department":"Acting","name":"Remy Ishak","original_name":"Remy Ishak","popularity":0.5204,"profile_path":"/4bMvXJaCNXtF2xmji1xXqYmSoxI.jpg","cast_id":2,"character":"","credit_id":"6a62c9a1176f7800f01afd02","order":0},{"adult":false,"gender":1,"id